  "response_text": "Inside a dim Long John Silver’s dining area at night, three young male-presenting employees sit around a small table under a hanging lamp. They wear matching light blue polo shirts and black baseball caps with the restaurant logo. One employee on the left looks down quietly, while the one on the right faces the table with a tray of food in front of him. On the table are a yellow Long John Silver’s cup, a ketchup bottle, and a paper-lined basket of fried food. Across from the employees sits a small puppet-like character, about tabletop height, with a tan face, round staring eyes, wild bright red hair sticking out in all directions, and furry brown hands. The puppet is dressed formally in a black suit jacket, white shirt, and dark tie, as if being coached for a performance.\n\nThe interaction focuses on the puppet and the employee seated opposite him. From over the employee’s shoulder, the puppet stands at the far side of the wooden table, facing him, while the food basket sits closer to the employee in the foreground. The puppet’s posture is alert and theatrical, with one hand on the table and its mouth moving as if trying to deliver a line. The young employee watches intently, his expression serious and instructive. The puppet reacts with exaggerated facial movements: its eyes widen, its mouth opens and closes, and its red hair flares around its head, making it look frantic and energetic.\n\nThe food is then presented in a glossy, carefully arranged close-up against a dark background. A paper-lined basket holds several golden-brown breaded fish strips in the foreground, a large pile of pale golden fries rising along the back, two round fried hushpuppies on the right, a small clear cup of white tartar sauce on the left, and a sprig of green parsley tucked behind the sauce. Crumbs and crunchy bits are scattered beneath the fish strips, emphasizing the fried coating. The basket liner includes small Long John Silver’s logos along the edges. The food fills the screen more and more closely, showing the rough, crisp breading on the fish strips and hushpuppies and the smooth white sauce in the cup.\n\nThe product arrangement widens to include a tall yellow drink cup standing behind the fries on the right. The cup is covered with visible condensation and has the colorful Long John Silver’s logo printed on it. The meal remains centered: fish strips across the front, fries fanning upward behind them, tartar sauce and parsley to the left, and hushpuppies to the right.\n\nThe scene returns to the restaurant table. The employee is again seen facing the puppet, with the basket of food partly visible near the bottom edge of the table. The puppet, still in its black suit, looks up at him with wide eyes. The employee’s expression softens into a patient, slightly weary look as he appears to prompt the puppet again. The puppet opens its mouth very wide, as if finally attempting the line with great effort. In close-up, its eyes bulge and its red hair sticks out wildly while it leans forward over the table, mouth stretched open in an exaggerated shout or confession. Its body dips lower toward the tabletop, still facing the employee, looking overwhelmed by the food and the coaching.\n\nThe commercial ends on a flat yellow background. Centered is the colorful Long John Silver’s logo. A moment later, black text appears beneath it reading, “HOW CAN YOU RESIST?”",
